content: <metadata>   <idinfo>     <citation>       <citeinfo>         <origin>Sanborn Colorado</origin>         <pubdate>20050804</pubdate>         <title>Contours</title>         <geoform>vector digital data</geoform>       </citeinfo>     </citation>     <descript>       <abstract>Aerial photography and scans will be acquired for a 359 square mile area encompassing the City and County of Denver, City of Glendale, City of Littleton, and the Denver Water Service Area. This project does not include DIA. Color 6" pixel resolution digital orthophotography, Digital Terrain Model, and 2' contours will be completed for the entire 359 sq miles, planimetric data capture will be completed for 152 square mile project area surrounding the City and County of Denver with a 1/4 mile buffer. True-ortho correction will be applied to all structures 4 stories and above where designated within a total of 3 square miles and include all bridges and highway overpasses.</abstract>       <purpose>To be used for elevation modelling and visualization.</purpose>       <supplinf>Two foot contours for Denver County excluding DIA.  Source Imagery for Compilation of Vector Data collection date - 3/26/2004.</supplinf>     </descript>     <timeperd>       <timeinfo>         <sngdate>           <caldate>unknown</caldate>         </sngdate>       </timeinfo>       <current>Unknown</current>     </timeperd>     <status>       <progress>Complete</progress>       <update>None planned</update>     </status>     <spdom>       <bounding>         <westbc>-105.115205</westbc>         <eastbc>-104.728895</eastbc>         <northbc>39.848145</northbc>         <southbc>39.609457</southbc>       </bounding>     </spdom>     <keywords>       <theme>         <themekt>None</themekt>         <themekey>topography</themekey>       </theme>       <theme>         <themekt>ISO 19115 Topic Categories</themekt>         <themekey>elevation</themekey>       </theme>       <place>         <placekt>None</placekt>         <placekey>Denver</placekey>         <placekey>Denver County</placekey>         <placekey>Colorado</placekey>         <placekey>USA</placekey>       </place>       <stratum>         <stratkt>None</stratkt>         <stratkey>DTM</stratkey>         <stratkey>Topographic</stratkey>         <stratkey>Planimetric</stratkey>       </stratum>       <temporal>         <tempkt>None</tempkt>         <tempkey>2004</tempkey>       </temporal>     </keywords>     <accconst>None</accconst>     <useconst>ACCESS CONSTRAINTS:   None. Note that for any item where attributes were derived from source material, the absolute accuracy will only be as good as the source material.</attraccr>     </attracc>     <logic>All vector data is validated using GIS software to ensure proper formatting as per the data base design. This validation procedure ensures correct physical format and field values for all elements.</logic>     <complete>All vector data goes through a visual quality inspection to ensure completeness. Note that because the data is being compiled from aerial photography, there amy be some areas where it is difficult to see the ground and as a result, some features may not be captured or captured incorrectly. These areas primarily pertain to areas where shadows, dense vegeation coverage or not visible areas (such as near large buildings) are located.</complete>     <posacc>       <horizpa>         <horizpar>The accuracy will meet or exceed the ASPRS Class 1 National Map Accuracy Standards for the scale of this project (1" = 100') and be sufficient to generate 2 foot contours.</horizpar>         <qhorizpa>           <horizpav>1.6 Feet</horizpav>           <horizpae>NMAS limiting RMSE in X or Y for well defined planimetric features.
